# Complete Data Flow

The following diagram shows the complete system workflow.

```text
User
  ↓
Lightning Web Component
  ↓
JavaScript Controller
  ↓
Apex Controller
  ↓
Salesforce Database
  ↓
Validation Rules
  ↓
Flow Automation
  ↓
Database Update
  ↓
Response to Apex
  ↓
LWC Refresh
  ↓
Updated UI
```

## Step-by-Step Explanation

### Step 1

User enters customer or opportunity data.

### Step 2

LWC captures user interaction.

### Step 3

JavaScript sends data to Apex.

### Step 4

Apex processes business logic.

### Step 5

Validation Rules verify data quality.

### Step 6

Records are saved in Salesforce.

### Step 7

Flows execute automation tasks.

### Step 8

Updated information is returned to the UI.

### Step 9

Users view updated records and dashboards.

